\begin{cor}
Corollary 1.6.1. Let \( M_1 \) and \( M_2 \) be any two affine sets in \( R^n \) of the same dimension. Then there exists a one-to-one affine transformation \( T \) of \( R^n \) onto itself such that \( TM_1 = M_2 \).
\end{cor}

proof:
\begin{proof}
Proof. Any \( m \)-dimensional affine set can be expressed as the affine hull of an affinely independent set of \( m + 1 \) points, and affine hulls are preserved by affine transformations. \(\|\)
\end{proof}

